<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-10-01T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-10-01T15:00:00-05:00" n="175" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d175">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">511.3B1/1: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate
                            Peace</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-10-01T16:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">October 1,
                                        1919—4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>3293. Your 4198, September 13th, midnight.<note n="56" xml:id="d175fn56">Not printed.</note></p>
                        <p>French Embassy states it has information that American military
                            authorities have disposed of arms or munitions to Spain, contrary to
                            understanding expressed in protocol.<note n="57" xml:id="d175fn57">Protocol of Sept. 10, <hi rend="italic">supra.</hi></note></p>
                        <pb facs="0295" n="197" xml:id="pg_197"/>
                        <p>Please advise American military authorities and place text of Convention
                            and protocol at their disposal.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>